# Privacy Policy
Effective date: July 10, 2026
This Privacy Policy explains how the Face Massage Coach mobile application ("App", "we", "us", or "our") collects, uses, and protects information when you use the App.
This document is provided for general informational purposes and should be reviewed by a qualified legal professional before publication.
## 1. Who We Are
Face Massage Coach is a mobile application that provides educational face massage guidance, session flows, and optional augmented reality guidance.
## 2. Important Health and Privacy Notice
The App is not a medical device and does not provide medical advice, diagnosis, treatment, rehabilitation, or prevention of any disease or condition.
The App may use the device camera and ARKit features to display guidance overlays. Face tracking and camera processing are intended to happen on the device. We do not intentionally collect, store, or transmit face scans, biometric templates, facial geometry, photos, videos, or camera images from the App.
You should not use the App as a substitute for professional medical advice. Consult a qualified doctor or healthcare professional before using the App, especially if you have any medical condition, skin condition, recent surgery, pain, inflammation, pregnancy-related concerns, neurological symptoms, facial implants, injections, dental issues, or any other health concern.
## 3. Information We Collect
We do not require you to create an account to use the App.
Depending on how you use the App, the following categories of information may be collected:
- App usage information, such as opened screens, selected massage programs, session starts and completions, tab openings, button taps, and similar in-app events.
- Device and technical information, such as device model, operating system version, app version, language, region, approximate diagnostics, and performance information.
- Crash and diagnostics information, such as crash logs, stack traces, device state at the time of a crash, and related technical data.
- Advertising-related information, such as advertising identifiers, ad impressions, clicks, approximate location inferred from IP address, and ad performance data, where permitted by law and platform settings.
- Local app state stored on your device, such as completed session counters, streak information, and last selected program.
We do not intentionally collect:
- Your name, address, phone number, email address, or account credentials.
- Photos, videos, audio recordings, or camera images.
- Biometric identifiers or biometric templates.
- Health records or medical documents.
- Payment card information.
## 4. Third-Party Services
The App uses third-party services that may collect and process data under their own privacy policies:
### Firebase Analytics
We use Firebase Analytics to understand how users interact with the App, improve features, measure engagement, and detect issues. Firebase Analytics may collect app usage events, device information, app instance identifiers, and related analytics data.
Firebase Privacy Policy: https://firebase.google.com/support/privacy
### Firebase Crashlytics
We use Firebase Crashlytics to detect, investigate, and fix crashes and technical errors. Crashlytics may collect crash logs, device information, operating system version, app version, stack traces, and diagnostic data.
Firebase Crashlytics information: https://firebase.google.com/products/crashlytics
### Google AdMob
We use Google AdMob to display advertisements in the App. AdMob and its partners may collect and process advertising identifiers, device information, ad interaction data, approximate location, and other data to deliver, measure, and improve ads, including personalized ads where allowed and consented to.
Google Privacy Policy: https://policies.google.com/privacy  
Google Ads settings: https://adssettings.google.com/
## 5. Camera and AR Data
The App may request camera permission to provide AR face guidance. Camera access is used to display guide lines and visual instructions on your face in real time.
We do not intentionally upload, store, sell, or share camera images, video, facial scans, or facial geometry. AR processing is intended to be performed locally on your device through Apple system frameworks.
If you deny camera permission, AR features may not work, but other parts of the App may remain available.
## 6. How We Use Information
We use collected information to:
- Provide and operate the App.
- Improve App performance, stability, design, and user experience.
- Understand which features and programs are used.
- Count and analyze completed sessions.
- Detect and fix crashes, bugs, and technical problems.
- Display, personalize, limit, and measure advertisements where permitted.
- Comply with legal obligations and enforce our rights.
## 7. Legal Bases Where Applicable
Where laws such as the GDPR or UK GDPR apply, we may process information based on:
- Your consent, for example for personalized ads or analytics where consent is required.
