- Performance of a contract, where processing is needed to provide the App.
- Compliance with legal obligations.
You may withdraw consent where applicable through device settings, App Tracking Transparency prompts, advertising settings, or consent forms shown in the App.
## 8. Advertising and Tracking Choices
Depending on your region and device settings, you may be asked whether you allow tracking or personalized advertising.
You can control advertising preferences through:
- iOS Settings > Privacy & Security > Tracking.
- iOS Settings > Privacy & Security > Apple Advertising.
- Google Ads settings: https://adssettings.google.com/
- Any consent form shown inside the App, where available.
If you disable tracking or personalized ads, you may still see ads, but they may be less relevant.
## 9. Data Sharing
We do not sell your personal information in the ordinary meaning of selling data for money.
Information may be shared with:
- Service providers that help us operate analytics, crash reporting, advertising, hosting, and diagnostics.
- Advertising partners involved in serving and measuring ads.
- Authorities, regulators, courts, or other parties when required by law or necessary to protect rights, safety, and security.
- Successors in connection with a merger, acquisition, restructuring, or transfer of the App.
Third-party services may process data independently under their own terms and privacy policies.
## 10. Data Retention
We retain information only for as long as reasonably necessary for the purposes described in this Privacy Policy, unless a longer retention period is required or permitted by law.
Retention periods for analytics, crash, and advertising data may also be controlled by Firebase, Google, AdMob, and other third-party service providers.
Local app data stored on your device may remain until you delete the App, reset the data, or clear device storage.
## 11. International Data Transfers
Third-party services used by the App may process information on servers located in different countries. These countries may have different data protection laws than your country of residence.
Where required, third-party providers are responsible for using appropriate safeguards for international transfers.
## 12. Children's Privacy
The App is not intended for children under 13 years old, or under the minimum age required by the laws of your country.
We do not knowingly collect personal information from children. If you believe a child has provided personal information through the App, contact us and we will take reasonable steps to delete it.
## 13. Your Rights
Depending on your location, you may have rights to:
- Access personal information about you.
- Request correction or deletion.
- Object to or restrict certain processing.
- Withdraw consent.
- Request data portability.
- Lodge a complaint with a data protection authority.
To exercise rights, contact us. We may need to verify your request.
## 14. Security
We use reasonable technical and organizational measures intended to protect information. However, no method of transmission or storage is completely secure, and we cannot guarantee absolute security.
You are responsible for maintaining the security of your device, operating system, and app permissions.
## 15. Changes to This Privacy Policy
We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. Updates will be posted in the App, on our website, or in the app store listing where appropriate.
Your continued use of the App after changes become effective means you accept the updated Privacy Policy, where permitted by law.



